text: Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 10:24 PM Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 10:24 PM JACKSONVILLE — Sara Worrell combined for 2 points, 1 ace, 10 assists and 2 digs for Jacksonville Routt in their loss to Hardin Calhoun 25-18, 25-17 on Wednesday. Caroline Casler led the Rockets with 6 digs, while Marie Langdon led the team with 4 kills. With the loss, Jacksonville Routt falls to 10-13 on the season. Raiders top Cyclones It took three games, but Quincy Notre Dame managed a narrow 23-25, 25-15, 25-19 victory over hosts Sacred Heart-Griffin Wednesday. Alli Lanzotti led the Cyclones with 13 assists, while also adding 6 digs. Elise Cummins also added the effort with 7 kills and 2 blocks. With the loss, SHG falls to 19-7 on the season. Crusaders ground Hawks RIVERTON — Kiersten Anderson’s outstanding game of 21 kills, 18 assists, 3 blocks, and 11 digs helped lead Lutheran over hosts Riverton 23-25, 25-16, 25-13 on Wednesday. Bailey Rexroad led the way for Riverton, combining for 12 kills, 8 assists, and 2 blocks. Adriana Ray (Riverton) and Katie Elmore (Lutheran) both led their teams with 14 digs. With the win, Lutheran improves to 14-12, while Riverton falls to 7-19 on the season. The State Journal-Register
